In [3]:
def vacancy(position, radius):
    @pb.site_state_modifier
    def modifier(state, x, y):
        x0, y0 = position
        state[(x-x0)**2 + (y-y0)**2 < radius**2] = False
        return state
    return modifier
In [59]:
model = pb.Model(
    graphene.monolayer_4atom(),
    pb.rectangle(x=2, y=1.5), 
    #vacancy(position=[0.5, 0], radius=0.1),
    #vacancy(position=[0, 0.1], radius=0.1),
    pb.translational_symmetry(a1=1, a2=False)

)
plt.figure(figsize=[10,20])
model.plot()
model.lattice.plot_vectors(position=[0.6, -0.25])
plt.show()


plt.figure()
solver = pb.solver.arpack(model, k=20)#, sigma = 1)  # for the 20 lowest energy eigenvalues
eigenvalues = solver.calc_eigenvalues(map_probability_at=[0.1, 0.6])  # position in [nm]
eigenvalues.plot_heatmap(show_indices=True)
pb.pltutils.colorbar()
plt.show()

plt.figure()
probability_map = solver.calc_probability(4)
probability_map.plot()
plt.show()

plt.figure()
dos = solver.calc_dos(energies=np.linspace(-pi/2, pi/2, 200), broadening=0.05)  # [eV]
dos.plot()
plt.show()


plt.figure()

kpm = pb.kpm(model)

ldos = kpm.calc_ldos(energy=np.linspace(-pi/2,pi/2, 500), broadening=0.015, position=[0, 0])
ldos.plot()
plt.show()

plt.figure()
plt.title('Eigenvalues')
plt.ylim(-pi/2,pi/2)
solver = pb.solver.lapack(model)
a = graphene.a_cc * sqrt(3)  # ribbon unit cell length
bands = solver.calc_bands(-pi/a, pi/a)
bands.plot()
plt.show()
